# __PKG_NAME__

A minimal [BigConfig](https://www.bigconfig.ai) package, scaffolded from the
`create-py-bigconfig-package` skill. It depends on the BigConfig Python SDK
(`big-config`) and renders one template through a single `hello` stage.

## Commands

```bash
uv sync
uv run pytest -q
uv run __PKG_NAME__ help               # run the CLI via the installed entry point
uv run python run package validate
uv run python run package describe
uv run python run package build
uv run python run package create     # safe demo create; renders hello
uv run python run package delete     # explicit no-op
```

## Layout

```
__PKG_NAME__/python/
├── run                       # launcher entry point (copied by bc-pkg; safe defaults only)
├── pyproject.toml            # one root manifest; ships src/__PKG_MODULE__ + src/resources
├── src/
│   ├── __PKG_MODULE__/
│   │   ├── cli.py            # main(argv, opts) dispatcher
│   │   ├── options.py        # profiles + active profile (`bb`)
│   │   ├── params.py         # BC_PAR_* overrides -> opts
│   │   ├── tools.py          # the `hello` render stage
│   │   ├── validation.py     # pure validate report + workflow step
│   │   ├── describe.py       # pure describe report + workflow step
│   │   ├── package.py        # lifecycle verbs + __PKG_MODULE___star wrapper
│   │   └── interop.py        # alias <-> namespaced-key bridge
│   └── resources/__PKG_NS_PATH__/tools/hello/greeting.txt
└── tests/
```

## Grow it

- Add params to the profile in `options.py` (and `DEFAULT_PROFILE` in `run`), keeping
  keys kebab-case to match template variables.
- Add a stage: write a render function in `tools.py`, `register_workflow_step` it,
  and add it to the `build` and `create` pipelines (and any real `delete` pipeline)
  in `package.py`.
- Override any param at runtime with `BC_PAR_*` env vars (e.g. `BC_PAR_NAME=alice`).
- Generated output lands in `.dist/` — never edit it as source.
